@wesearl91: To prevent the slide from changing on every in-out movement, you can use a timer, like so:
javascript
var hoverTimer = 0; 
$(document).on('mouseenter', function() {
    $slides.superslides('stop');
    clearTimeout(hoverTimer);
});
$(document).on('mouseleave', function() {
    hoverTimer = setTimeout(function(){
        $slides.superslides('start');
    }, 2000); 
});
After examining your content for a while, user will realize that the slide is on pause. At this point, it is likely that she has lost track of pausing time, and has been expecting the next slide for a little while. So she will click to move on to the next one. If she move her cursor out of this fullscreen slide to let it autoplay, I think we should wait for just a little (3-4 seconds remaining time are too long) and resume sliding.
