. Solution found! To anyone interested animating the contents of the current slide in both events (animated.slides and animating.slides) here is an example code that will fadeIn the container div (with text, captions etc.) of each current slide and fadeOut the container div when the slide is 
MARKUP
The only thing that you need to change on your HTML markup is to add the same class for all divs inside the .slides-container. I added the class ".slide" for my solution to target the slides.
ANIMATED SLIDES (Function call when animation of a slide is complete)
$(document).on('animated.slides', function() {
  var currentSlide = $('#slides').data('superslides').current; //Get the index number of the current slide
  var $this = $('.slides-container .slide').eq(currentSlide); //Var of the current slide as element by index using the     variable currentSlide inside eq().
   $('.container', $this).fadeTo(300,1); //Target the container div of the current slide and fade to 1.
});
ANIMATING SLIDES (Function call while slide animation happens) 
$(document).on('animating.slides', function() {
  var currentSlide = $('#slides').data('superslides').current; // Get the index number of the current slide
  var $this = $('.slides-container .slide').eq(currentSlide); // Var of the current slide as element by index using the     variable currentSlide inside eq().
  $('.container', $this).fadeTo(300,0); Target the container div of the current slide and fade to 1.
});
