I had the same issue. There is a fancy box and superslides only uses one image and has no right-left control but when key navigations are used it slides image right or left. If fadeIn effect is active superslides image is gone.
I added keys: false in the options and wrapped the function to handle the keys like below:
if(that.options.keys){
    $(document).on('keyup', function(e) {
      if (e.keyCode === 37) {
        that.animate('prev');
      }
      if (e.keyCode === 39) {
        that.animate('next');
      }
    });
}
