zamber:
You're stacking multiple event calls one after another. Try something like this:
```
var $slides = $('.large');
var isAnimating = false;
$slides.bind('animating.slides', function() { isAnimating = true; });
$slides.bind('animated.slides', function() { isAnimating = false; });
$('.item').mouseenter(function() {
  if (!isAnimating) {
    $slides.superslides('animate', ($(this).data('slide')));
  }
});
```
Now close this issue as this is not a support forum but an issue tracker.
. Use https://api.jquerymobile.com/swipe/ or any other swipe event handler. In the handler call $('#slides').superslides('animate', 'next']). Do the back swipe handler the same way but call 'prev'.
This is not an issue with the slider but with your understanding of how it works. Close this issue.
